-- Manulife's U.S. unit to buy New York Life's retirement business
-- By Manya Venkatesh in Bengaluru
-- Tue Dec 23, 2014 02:25PM EST
-- None



Dec 23 (Reuters) - Largest Canadian insurer Manulife Financial Corp's <MFC.TO> U.S. unit will buy New York Life Insurance Co's retirement services business for an undisclosed amount.

New York Life will assume 60 percent of certain life insurance policies of Manulife's U.S. unit, John Hancock Financial, on a reinsurance basis, the Canadian company said. [ID:nPnbd2ST1] Manulife did not disclose the financial details of the deal.